                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS BOYCE. I am a constable of Hampsted district. On the evening of the 6th of August I saw the prisoner in company with another boy go into Mosely's shop- the other boy took down a cage, which had white mice in it, and the prisoner took down a pair of skates - I pursued him, and took him to the watch-house; I found the skates on him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The prosecutor took the value of the property, and here is the paper he signed for it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-343-person2464">
                  THOMAS 
                  MOSELY
               <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2464" type="surname" value="MOSELY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2464" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2464" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have not been paid for them - I know nothing of this paper, and never saw it before; I did not sign this paper - I know nobody who lives in Tothill-street; as far as I am concerned this paper is a forgery altogether; the prisoner's friends came and offered me money to keep from here, but I refused it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-343-person2465">
                  JOSEPH 
                  GATES
               <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2465" type="surname" value="GATES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2465" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2465" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prisoner's brother. 
               <persName id="t18310908-343-person2466">
                  Thomas 
                  Mosely
               <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2466" type="surname" value="Mosely"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2466" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2466" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             signed that paper, and took 2s. from me, being the full value of the property; he told me if I would give him 5s. to pay his expences to save him coming here, he would accept of it - he took 2s., and we spent 3s. in drink; I, him, and another friend.</p>
               <p>THOMAS MOSELY. I never drank with this man in my life, or spent 3s. in his compary, nor received 2s. from him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-343-person2467">
                  JOSEPH 
                  GATES
               <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2467" type="surname" value="GATES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2467" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2467" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My friends are all gone home, or I could bring them up - they saw us drinking together,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183109080146"></xptr>down by the Sessions'-house, I do not know the sign -Mr. Lewis, the prosecutor, and Mr. and Mrs. Mason were there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-343-person2468">
                  FREDERICK 
                  HAYES
               <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2468" type="surname" value="HAYES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2468" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2468" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoemaker, and live in Chapel-street, Somers'-town. The prosecutor told me he had taken 2s. of this man - I did not write this paper; I saw it at the Northampton Arms, Pentonville - the prosecutor was there, drinking with Mr. Meares and two young men; Meares in a bird fancier, at Pentonville - I saw the paper in Lewis' hands; Lewis wrote the body of it, and Mosely put his name to it, but not in my presence.</p>
               <p>Q. Look at this paper, is not the whole of it in one handwriting? A. I should not think the name was written by the same person - I was not present when it was written at all; the prosecutor told me he had received the 2s., and did not want to hurt the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-343-person2469">
                  JOSEPH 
                  GATES
               <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2469" type="surname" value="GATES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2469" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-343-person2469" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . We were drinking at the Northampton Arms, as well as at Clerkenwell - we met at the Sessions'-house, and drank; we finished at the Northampton Arms.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-343-verdict1767" type="verdictDescription">
